==Old English==
===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /æarm/

===Etymology 1===
From Germanic ''*arma-'', from Indo-European ''*armo-'', from ''*ar-, *arə-'' ‘fit, join’.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[arm]], Old Saxon [[arm]] (Dutch [[arm]]), Old High German [[arm]] (German [[Arm]]), Old Norse [[armr]] (Swedish [[arm]]), Gothic [[𐌰𐍂𐌼𐍃]].  The IE root is also the source of Old Church Slavonic [[рамо]] (Russian [[рамо]] ‘shoulder’), Latin [[armus]].

====Noun====
